<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>
<body>
  <tal:tag condition="view/update"/>
  <metal:heading fill-slot="pageheading">
    <h1>Select a new translation group</h1>
  </metal:heading>

  <div metal:fill-slot="main">

    <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_editform/editform">

      <p metal:fill-slot="extra_info">
        Select the translation group that will be responsible for translations
        in <tal:distro replace="context/title">Ubuntu Linux</tal:distro>,
        and the translation permissions used by the distribution.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div metal:fill-slot="help">
    <p>
      Here you can assign a translation group to work on translating the
      <tal:distro replace="context/displayname">Ubuntu</tal:distro>
      distribution.  Once a translation group is assigned to the distribution,
      you can also select how open the translation work should be to
      contributions from others.
    </p>
    <p>
      A translation group is a collection of translators that works together on
      projects, translating into one or more languages.  Go to the
      <a href="/translations/groups/">translation groups overview</a> page to
      create and manage translation groups.
    </p>
    <ul class="info">
      <li>
        <a href="https://help.launchpad.net/RosettaFAQ"
        >Frequently asked questions</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
